			<ns0:name>s...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108394971971967673680/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">What we must do is have the front end uniformly mark parameter passing independently of the target ABI.  And the backend must be solely responsible for the mapping between parameters passing and the target ABI, which is compatible with the respective ABIs implemented by nacl-gcc.  As a general rule it is much easier to lower a by-value structure to be passed by address than to recover an address taking and indirection back to by value.  So in the absence of concrete evidence to the contrary, the front end should emit bitcode that reflects by-value passing as by-value bitcode.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-08-30T03:02:39.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-08-30T03:02:39.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 12 by s...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2207#c12" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2207/comments/full/12" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>